Get started with Amazon EKS â€“ eksctl
Prerequisites:
1. kubectl is installed
2. eksctl is installed
3. awscli is installed & configured with proper permissions

AWS Account Profiles:
aws configure list-profiles  #This will show you the aws configures profiles
aws sts get-caller-identity #this will show you the account id
aws configure get region --profile default # This will show the current region you're in
aws configure list --profile default #This will show the current profile details

step-1: creating amazon eks cluster and nodes
command: eksctl create cluster --name my-eks-cluster --region us-east-1
command: eksctl create cluster --name my-eks-cluster --region us-east-1 --fargate

step2: View and update the context in terminal (kubectl)
command: kubectl config current-context
command: aws eks update-kubeconfig --name my-eks-cluster --region us-east-1
command: kubectl config current-context
command: eksctl get clusters

step3: view the kubenetes nodes
command: kubectl get nodes -o wide
command: kubectl get pods -A -o wide

step4:
command: eksctl delete cluster --name my-ekscluster --region us-east-1


